Congrats SC, we did it! Another successful week in the books. As we reflect, we realize that in-person learning has become a PRIVILEGE, not a right. With so many districts forced to all remote, here we are. Our fate depends on you. If u continue to stay humble, put politics aside and follow all safety protocols outside of school, we can continue to provide this PRIVILEGE to all of our students because they deserve it! Please repost and start the movement. #SCTogether
#MaskUp #Humility #PrideandExcellence

post_text:
SC Running Rebels Cross Country featured by IHSA. Congrats Ladies and Coach Rennick!

https://ilxctf.runnerspace.com/profile.php?member_id=42240&do=news&news_id=607351

The Stark County Lady Rebels cross country team has been included in Mike Newman‚Äôs ILXCTF Girls IHSA Class 1A Cross Country Season Preview. The feature ranks the top 30 cross country teams in Class 1A and lists the top 20 teams in the state that although not ranked, are the top contenders to qualify for the State Series. The Lady Rebels have been included as one of the top contenders to qualify for State this season, which recognizes them as one of the top 50 class 1A cross country teams in the state. It is an accomplishment simply to be included in the preview and further motivation to the team for this coming season.

Our first race will be August 26th 2020 at 4:00 p.m. on our home course at the Stark County High School, when the girls begin their defense of their 2019 LTC Conference Championship.

Pride & Excellence! Go Lady Rebels!!!





#SoProud #Culture #PrideandExcellence

JUNIOR HIGH and HIGH SCHOOL Students and staff-

It's wonderful that we can provide free lunch to all students! To keep track of who is taking advantage and to make sure that lunch is delivered to your 7th hour class, any day that you would like lunch, you will need to fill out the lunch count form. The form will be will be available via your school e-mail, the school website, and this link:

https://bit.ly/SCJHHSLC

It will need to be filled out EVERYDAY you would like a lunch. Thanks!

Junior High Baseball and Softball Practice:

When: Starting Wednesday the 5th from 10am-Noon Monday-Friday.

Where: Baseball at the Fairgrounds and Softball at Duryea Park.

What to bring: water bottle, towel, and mask.

We will start with 7th and 8th graders - the 6th graders will be invited to join if there are not enough 7th and 8th graders participating.

What's also needed: students need a sports physical or they can not practice. (Free sports physicals today in the HS gym - JH @ 4:30pm and HS @ 5pm. Refer to the Facebook post for more information).

post_text:
We will be offering free sports physicals for Stark County students going into 7th, 8th, 10th, 11th, and 12th grade on Monday, August 3rd. Starting at 4:30 will be Jr high with High school starting at 5 (Provider will be there at 5). We just need time to have students ready for her when she arrives.

We are asking them to come thru HS gym entrance.
Temps will be checked at the door
Must wear a mask
Follow the 6 ft social distancing rule.

** 6th grader's "normal" physical to enter 6th grade will be used for sport physicals.

Pre-participation forms can be picked up at the HS/Jr High office, off the school web site, or at the door the day of our clinic. Form must be completed and signed by a parent before we can do the physical.

post_text:
Join me in welcoming Mrs. Down as our new 5th grade teacher! Mrs. Down is married to her high school sweetheart, TJ, and they have 2 children. Luke is 5 years old and Drew is 4 years old. She is a Toulon native. Mrs. Down enjoys traveling, playing games, crafting, and being outside with her boys.

Mrs. Down graduated from Monmouth College with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Elementary Education with a Language Arts Middle School endorsement. She completed her Master of Arts degree in Differentiated Instruction from Concordia University in June. Mrs. Down taught for 12 years in Kewanee #229. She taught 3rd grade for 9 years and 4th grade for 3 years. She is very excited to be a REBEL again. #sceslearners #RollSC #relationships #culture

post_text:
Mrs. Duckworth is our new third grade teacher at SCES this year! Mrs. Duckworth is married to her high school sweetheart, Jeremy, and they have four children who are 11, 9, 8, & 4. They also have a cavapoo named Charlie. She lives by a lake outside of Princeville. She is also a travel consultant and specializes in planning Disney Vacations! She loves making people smile and always tries to look on the bright side! Mrs. Duckworth likes to travel, bake, read, play games, and spend time with family and friends. She has previously coached junior high volleyball and loves watching sports. She is a fan of the Bears, Cubs, and Illini.

Mrs. Duckworth graduated from Illinois State University with a degree in Early Childhood Education. She taught in Princeville for 14 years, and has taught all grades 3rd through Pre-K. Mrs. Duckworth says, "I am excited to be teaching 3rd grade again, now at Stark County! (Red is one of my favorite colors!)"

Join me in wishing Mrs. Duckworth a warm Rebel welcome!
#RollSC #sceslearners #culture #relationships

Stark County Board of Education will begin a new tradition on July 2O, 2020. Added to the monthly Board Meeting Agenda will be the Pride and Excellence Contibution Recognition. This honor is intended to honor students, staff, parents and/or community members who positively contribute the The Pride and Excellence of Stark County. See you tomorrow night at 6:15 pm at the Elementary School Cafeteria.

post_text: IHSA UPDATE JULY 14, 2020
text: IHSA UPDATE JULY 14, 2020

post_text:
We will be sharing a draft of our Stark County Reopening of School Plan at the end of this week. The plan was developed by the Stark County Reopening School Task Force made up of teachers, support staff, parents, district and building administrators, board members, nurses and select student leaders. The use of staff and parent surveys helped guide our planning and research. Guidelines from the ISBE, IDPH and local Health Department were utilized for student and staff safety while maximizing in person instruction. The plan will be presented to the Board of Education on Monday July 20th for adoption. Your patience, flexibility and support is appreciated as all plans will be fluid up to and into the school year as guidelines and restrictions continue to change from State and Health Officials.
#PrideandExcellence #Relentless #Process #PHEARCE

Kindergarten Registration!

We would much rather have celebrated our new kindergartners in person at our Round-Up, but we're still excited to welcome our new learners!

If you are a resident of Stark County CUSD 100 and your child was born on or before September 1, 2015, it's time to sign them up for kindergarten for the 2020-2021 school year! Children who attended SC preschool should register on Skyward. If you are a parent/guardian of a NEW kindergartner, please let us know by filling out this Google Form: https://forms.gle/jCFQgxAqz7otfwV77!

For an informational letter, visit stark100.com!

post_text:
Our SCES librarian, Mrs. Kelly, has been asked by several parents about books that would be good to share with their children addressing race inequality, racism, and diversity so here are some things she'd like to share with you all:
Some personal favorites are:
Martin Rising by Andrea Davis Pinkney
Booked, Crossover, and How to Read a Book by Kwame Alexander
Child of the Civil Rights Movement by Paula Young Sheldon
New Kid by Jerry Kraft (A graphic novel that won this year's Newberry Award)
Last Stop on Market Street by Matt de la Pena (winner of the 2016 Newberry Award)

https://www.slj.com/?detailStory=great-books-social-justice-middle-grade
This list includes Front Desk by Kelly Yang that her 5th grade book club read and LOVED this year.

She's also including this podcast link:

https://longestshortesttime.com/episode-116-how-to-not-accidentally-raise-a-racist/

And this article:

https://www.todaysparent.com/family/parenting/how-to-talk-to-kids-about-racism-an-age-by-age-guide/

SLJ.COM

Schools will be set up for Chromebook return next Thursday, May 21st from 2-6 pm and Friday, May 22nd from 8am-4pm. You may return Chromebooks to either building.

At SCES: Enter red doors in the front of the building. An employee in the office will record your name and that you are returning a Chromebook and charger. They will buzz you in the building and you will drop the Chromebook(s) in the music room and exit through the exterior door to the parking lot.

At SCJH/HS: Please enter HS parking lot door. Go to the library door where a staff will record your name and that you have your Chromebook and charger. You‚Äôll leave the library out the other door and through the HS street doors.
